article.headline: Thomas adds 15 rebounds
article.linkText: No doubting Thomas: Georgia F has 27 in win
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. (AP) -- Christi Thomas had 27 points and 15 rebounds
to lead Georgia (No. 9 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to an 88-70 victory over Mississippi State in the Southeastern Conference opener for both Thursday night.

Thomas had a double-double 5½ minutes before halftime when she scored her 18th point off her 10th rebound on the putback off a
miss by Kara Braxton. That gave the Bulldogs a 37-18 lead.

Braxton and Cori Chambers added 12 points apiece, and Sherill
Baker had 11 for Georgia (12-2).

Tan White and Seneca Anderson scored 18 points apiece for
Mississippi State (5-8), which trailed by more than 20 for most of
the game. Georgia's biggest lead was 63-32 with 15:18 to play after
a putback by Braxton.

Mississippi State had no answer for Georgia's size, starting no
one taller than 6-foot. Georgia's 6-5 Thomas, 6-6 Braxton, 6-3
Rebecca Rowsey and 6-2 Jessica Pierce dominated the boards. The
Lady Bulldogs won the rebounding battle 46-36.

Georgia led 48-24 at the half while outrebounding State 30-15.
Georgia also hit 54 percent of its shots in the first half,
compared to 28 percent for State.

The rout started early, after Rebecca Kates hit a 3 for State
that put the visiting Lady Bulldogs up 7-6 with 16:10 to play.
Georgia scored 20 consecutive points over a five-minute stretch,
capped by Pierce's putback at 10:54 that made it 26-7.
